poon mixture inside traced circles on baking paper to form discs approx. 4-6 cm deep. Sprinkle cocoa powder over then lightly swirl through using a metal skewer. Bake for 10 minutes (150°C) then reduce oven temperature to 120°C and bake for a further 1 hour (120°C). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."},{"content":"Turn off oven and, with oven door kept closed, leave pavlova to cool completely (at least 3 hours, preferably overnight - see tip)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Topping"},{"content":"When ready to serve, <strong>insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream in mixing bowl and whisk <b>until soft peaks form\/speed 3<b>, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Place one pavlova disc on a cake stand then pile with the whipped cream and half the raspberries. Place second pavlova disc on top then scatter remaining raspberries over. Decorate with chocolate curls and serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use the base of a Ø 20 cm cake tin to mark out circles on baking paper in step 1.","Keeping the oven door closed and leaving the meringues to cool slowly will prevent them from cracking.","As with any whisked egg white recipe, make sure your mixing bowl and butterfly whisk are completely clean and dry before whisking."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","4h 40m","10 portions"]}